  "instructions": [
    "Drain the almonds and place them in a food processor with the citrus juices, garlic, mint, orange zest, and a pinch of salt.",
    "Blend until the mixture is crumbly but still holds together slightly. If it's too moist, add more almonds for better texture.",
    "Press the mixture into an 8x8 inch baking dish or tray lined with parchment paper.",
    "Bake at 170°C (325°F) for about 30 minutes until lightly golden and crispy on top."
